==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Shirr
<hw>Shirr</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Sewing)</fld> <def>A
series of close parallel runnings which are drawn up so as to make the
material between them set full by gatherings; -- called also
<altname>shirring</altname>, and <altname>gauging</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Shirred</ent>⟦br⟧
